examples.en: He peeped inquisitively into the drawer.
I'd have asked more questions, but I didn't want to seem inquisitive.
...an inquisitive woman who tends to everybody's business but her own...
In this inquisitive age, when the Alps are crested, and seas fathomed.
If someone saw a man climbing a light post they might get inquisitive.
She is like a wild young colt, very inquisitive but very coy and not to be easily cajoled.
